fields.title: The Grand Budapest Hotel
fields.review: An utter delight of a film that I continue to revisit on a regular basis. It might  actually be Wes Anderson's best movie, which is saying quite a lot.

fields.title: Interstellar
fields.review: Upon my rewatch I realized that this movie is a masterpiece. Christopher Nolan is a genius.

fields.title: La La Land
fields.review: I literally have not and will not ever see a movie better than this, we really do not deserve movies this good.

fields.title: Knives Out
fields.review: Wildly entertaining and seriously hilarious. The best popcorn movie of the year. Trully impressive. I had way too much fun to find any real issues with this.

fields.title: Everything Everywhere All at Once
fields.review: This is one of the best things I have ever seen in my piece of shit life. A rocks just made me cry.

fields.title: Thor: Love and Thunder
fields.review: The best and most visually interesting part of the movie was the different fonts they used for the credit.

fields.title: Whiplash
fields.review: My mind exploded watching this movie. My heart is still pounding. My body is still shivering.

fields.title: The Batman
fields.review: After sleeping on this, I can confirm this movie freaking bangs. It is one of those movies where the more you think about it, the better it is.

fields.title: Fight Club
fields.review: Had to sound like a teen cinephile but this movie is breathtaking. Love everything about this movie.

fields.title: Parasite
fields.review: Screaming, crying, this is the best movie that has ever happened, the film that truly made me a cinephile is the first foreign film to ever win best picture.
